and public utilities cases for his electricity clients in the colorado and wyoming supreme courts and other state and federal courts  he also appears before the public utilities commissions in colorado wyoming utah montana new mexico and idaho experienceexperiencerepresented clients in energy project development and the purchase or sale of electricity assisting them on contract negotiations rate proceedings regulatory issues electric transmission legislation and administrative agency issues arising out of the changing federal and state regulatory environment provides counsel and advocacy in administrative proceedings involving rate cases tariff issues construction projects resource planning and transmission qualifying facilities mergers and acquisitions service quality matters line extensions legislation environmental regulatory requirement demand side management client results client results represented a client coalition in a firstofitskind proceeding before a state utilities commission involving an electric utility’s proposed addition of expensive air quality controls for one of its aging coalfired power plants  the electric utility initially proposed to spend over 0 million for the air quality control equipment but an investigation by holland  hart and our team of expert witnesses into the costeffectiveness of the utility’s proposal ultimately led to finding a dramatically less expensive alternative for our clients and all of the utility’s other ratepayers over a sixstate region  due to its significantly lower cost the alternative solution ultimately selected will save the utility’s consumers including our client coalition over  million  represented a coalition of industrial electric consumers before a state utility commission in opposing an “allenergy” rate design proposed by an electric utility that would have dramatically increased rates for larger consumers  in appealing the initial ruling of the commission in favor of the utility mr pomeroy succeeded in having the unfavorable rate design overturned at both the state district court level and at the state supreme court resulting in a major victory for his clients represented a coalition of over 0 independent power producers– including both fossil fuel and renewable power plant developers – in opposing public service company of colorados psco proposal before the colorado public utilities commission puc for a complete exemption from colorados competitive bidding requirement for new power plants which if granted would have eliminated any business opportunity in colorado for nonutility power developers although no other party resisted the psco request for an exemption from bidding following three full weeks of contested hearings the puc ruled entirely in our client coalitions favor and required psco to compete with independent developers for new power plants the final order approved over  megawatts of new generation resources all of which were to be built by independent power producers providing several hundreds of millions of dollars in new business opportunities in colorado to our clients represented a major national wind developer in securing unanimous approval from the colorado public utilities commission of a 00mw wind farm in eastern colorado over the vigorous opposition of other parties to the case in that proceeding approval of the wind farm was contested by the staff of the colorado public utilities commission industrial consumers gas producers and other wind developers mr pomeroy served as lead counsel for the developer of the wind farm and developed and implemented a coordinated strategy with the local electric utility that secured the required commission approval after a contested hearing served as lead counsel for an industrial electric consumer client coalition in opposing a  million rate increase triggered by volatile power markets at the time of the failure of a major power plant by an electric utility  following an investigation into the cause of the power plant failure and into the power purchasing practices of the utility the holland  hart legal team secured a complete disallowance of the proposed rate increase an outcome which was ultimately upheld by the state supreme court saving his the members of his client coalition alone well over 0 million in annual electricity costs serves as lead counsel for a member coalition of large electric consumers the wyoming industrial energy consumers wiec in electric regulatory proceedings before the wyoming public service commission continuing a representation that began in  when he was selected by wiec as its legal counsel upon wiec’s formation  he has represented wiec in every major electric rate case since that time  for example in 0 and 0 rate cases the wiec legal team succeeded in reducing the final rate hike for consumers by more than onehalf cutting back the 0 rate increase from  million to only  million and 0 rate increases from  million to only  million resulting in annual total electric bill savings for our client coalition of over  million in each year spearheaded the formation of the largest and longestrunning industrial electric consumer coalitions in colorado montana and wyoming and for decades with other members of holland  hart has represented those coalitions before their respective state public utilities commissions  he has also served as lead counsel in the formation of independent power plant developer coalitions in new mexico and wyoming while serving as lead counsel for a similar coalition in colorado  in addition he has represented individual industrial electric consumers and individual independent power producers both fossil fuels and renewable in major electric regulatory proceedings and rate cases before state utilities commissions across the mountain west practices practices public utilities regulation environmental and natural resources news and insights news holland  hart colorado attorneys named to  best lawyers® list 0 speaking engagements energy i