pomeroy age  passed away peacefully surrounded by his family on nov  in woodland ca bob is survived by his daughter patricia pomeroy eisner married to charles eisner of walnut creek ca and his sons robert d pomeroy jr married to susan backus pomeroy of simsbury ct and j richard pomeroy married to susan damron pomeroy of woodland he was predeceased by his wife of  years mary morning pomeroy who died in  bob was a proud granddad gdad to his seven grandchildren daniel eisner married to theresa massagli eisner deborah eisner joffe married to joseph joffe jonathan eisner elizabeth pomeroy lipscomb married to stephen lipscomb sarah pomeroy wilson married to ryan wilson lauren damron kiesz married to christopher kiesz and claire morning pomeroy warren married to matthew warren bob also had six great grandchildren olivia and audrey kiesz james and mason lipscomb and leah and zoe joffe bobby dwight pomeroy later changed to robert was born in pittsburg no h kansas on dec  0 he moved with his family to long beach ca in  and lived in san bernardino where he met mary in  bob and mary were high school sweethearts and graduated from san bernardino high school in 7 and were active in christian endeavor bob attended uc berkeley and graduated from ucla in  before joining the us coast guard he served as an officer in world war ii helping build loran stations in the south pacific bob worked his entire career for the southern california gas company retiring as a vice president in  after  years bob and mary raised their family in glendale ca and were elders and deacons of the glendale presbyterian church they moved to woodland in  and were active in the yolo county history museum the woodland presbyterian church and the woodland sunrise rotary club bob led a life of service through the presbyterian church the exchange club of los angeles the boy scouts of america us coast guard and rotary he and the family loved to travel by car and trailer air or cruise ship visiting all 0 states and ma